article.headline: CS Bakersfield 60, NC A&amp,T 52
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- Javonte Maynor scored 19 points to lead Cal State Bakersfield over North Carolina A&T 60-52 Sunday night. Maynor was 5 of 10 from 3-point range. Corey Hall had 13 rebounds for the Roadrunners (6-10). The Aggies led 30-23 at halftime in a game with six lead changes. The Roadrunners shot 24 percent from the field in the first half, but improved in the second, shooting 42.9 percent. The Aggies, who shot 42.9 percent in the first half, dropped to 33 percent. The Roadrunners led in rebounds 42-31. Lamont Middleton had 12 points to lead the Aggies (5-9). Austin Witter had 11 points and blocked six shots. Adrian Powell had nine rebounds.
